{
  "texts": [
    "This framework focuses on extracting salient foreground regions and enhancing the detection of underwater objects.",
    "Mou et al. (2017) used the Harris angle detection operator to locate geometric centers and designed a simple linear iterative clustering method.",
    "Their approach achieves the effective detection of underwater objects by highlighting foreground targets while attenuating background areas.",
    "Zhou et al. (2019) introduced a composite convolutional neural network based on shared latent sparse features (SLS) and deep belief networks (DBN), thereby overcoming the lack of CNN training data by using texture images and optimizing and interfering with textures using SLS and DBN.",
    "Their proposed method enhances the performance of underwater object detection and classification."
  ]
}